2. Organize VAT staff learning mobility in partner organizations in Estonia and Austria;
3. Organize the working environment-based learning practices in companies in textildesign, clothing design and architecture sectors in Germany, the UK and Spain;
4.  To ensure the monitoring, support and monitoring for all participants of  mobility;
5. To ensure a transparent selection procedure in accordance with the selection criteria;
6. Ensure the appropriate specialty competences acquisition;
7. In collaboration with partner organizations develop a work plan and content to acquire certain competencies;
8. Encourage the process of identification and documentation of acquired competencies in the Europass Mobility document and CV
9. To integrate in learning process acquired knowledge, skills, competencies and attitudes to improve the qualifications and professional practice course content, cooperation with employers;
10. Get to know the local culture, understand intercultural interaction and impact of global processes;
11. To promote Erasmus + mobility among pupils, staff, graduates and other stakeholders.

Sending organization is LMMDV.
Project hosting organizations are:
1. Tartu art school, Estonia
2. Wiener Kunstschule, Austria
3. Escola Artística de Soares dos Reis, Portugal
4. OMNIA the joint authority of education in Espoo region, Finland
