The AVE PLUS II Project aims to promote the mobility of learners for learning purposes, as well as meeting the needs identified in the Ave Region. It involves a consortium of 13 schools: Didáxis Cooperativa de Ensino ; Cenatex – Escola Profissional; Escola Secundária Martins Sarmento; Agrupamento de Escolas Gonçalo Sampaio; Externato de S. Miguel de Refojos; Agrupamento de Escolas Camilo Castelo Branco e OFICINA Escola Profissional do Instituto Nun'Alvres; Escola Profissional Cisave AE Francisco de Holanda, AE Santos Simões, AE Fafe, Escola Profissional Bento de Jesus Graça, AE Padre Benjamim Salgado.
Education, Training and Promotion of working experiences are crucial for the development of the Ave region. By Knowing the advantages of the ERASMUS + programme to  foster  exchange,  cooperation  and  mobility between  education  and  professional  training  systems and its contribution to the social and professional development of their participants, CIM do Ave presents this proposal.
 The main aim is to meet the needs and gaps of the Region and improve the performance, quality and attractiveness of education and professional training in Europe, while at the same time encouraging the use of various professional training opportunities in the context of lifelong learning.
Main Aims: 
•  Promote work experiences with new training opportunities for the acquisition of specific professional skills;
•  Increasing the employability of young people in the labour market that is  increasingly global and competitive;
•  Improve the relationship between training and labour market;
•  Increase the level of personal and professional development of the participants;
• Promote the international partnership networks;
•  Strengthen the quality of school organization and promote the visibility of the schools;;
•  Promote the Vocational Education as an alternative quality;
• encourage innovation and entrepreneurship, 
• Contribute to a European awareness that leads to an active and participatory citizenship
The present project is addressed to vocational trainees divided equal in number by each consortium of schools. Thus, each school will send 8 trainees from different professional training courses. This project aims to give an opportunity for participants with vocational training of performing an international internship; and to 20 professionals (teachers and staff) in order to support their personal and professional development to improve future activities.
By participating in this project, the participants will achieve the following objectives: a) consolidate knowledge; b) acquire new skills and become more competitive in the labour market access; c) learn or improve a new language; d) get in touch with the labour market; e) the acquisition of new forms of communication, relationship with other cultures, and the integration on the real European common market. 
At the end of the project we expect to have been able to build a partnership that does not  finishes with the end of the project, but that is maintained with mutual benefits of networking by sharing knowledge, experiences, needs and goals. Our second goal is to help the recognition of Europe as a space of all citizens, with more mobility on employment and training. Finally, we intend to help participants achieving their career goals, as well as a deep consciousness that mobility experiences are increasingly needed to be competitive in the labour market.
We believe that this project will be an asset to the plan of activities of the CIM do AVE, particularly regarding to the Plan for the Inclusive Growth of the AVE and Vocational Training. It will provide to young people and to staff of the region important solutions to their real training needs and it will be a complement to their experience to enable them to face the labour market with more optimistic perspectives.
The program will be carried during 24 months and the mobility period for each trainee will be 3 months. The Participants will have preparation before the departure, cultural preparation , socio-cultural activities, internships in selected companies according to each participant's profile, monitoring, mentoring and continuous evaluation throughout the program and collection and evaluation of the results obtained and the labour integration rate.

The project “New Skills for the future III” is based on the principle that a capable and competent professional has, today (and tomorrow), technical and personal characteristics different from the ones that were valued a few years ago. It is currently valued technical knowledge, acquired through formal learning, but also the experiences of non-formal and informal learning, desirably transversal. Personally, we pursue autonomy and responsibility but also flexibility, dynamism and proactivity, abandoning the idea of a "job for life".
Therefore, in a complex, changing labour market where it is not always easy for young people to enter, due to their lack of experience, there is a need to provide young people with differentiating tools for the transition to working life.
With this project we aim to enable 35 students and recent graduates from ATEP professional courses (level IV of the European Qualifications Framework) to contact with the world of work abroad (Spain, France, Germany and England), through traineeships in a partner entity. 
With this experience we intend to develop student´s employability profile in order to facilitate their entry into the world of work, namely:
- develop autonomy and responsibility, just by being "outside"; 
- develop technical skills in a particular area of learning; 
- develop interpersonal skills through social contacts; 
- contact with a foreign language and culture as a way to differentiate their learning and experience over other job applicants; 
- raising awareness of the possibility of working abroad.
The project also includes the possibility of 4 of its teachers of technical areas to carry out training aboard and 4 staff member (teachers and non-teachers) do job shadowing in vocational school, in order to develop its technical profile, namely:
- contact with other realities and different ways of working;
- upgrade technical skills in a particular area;
- promote contact with a foreign language and culture;
- improve their technical skills, bringing benefits to the process of teaching-learning (only teachers).
To develop this project, ATEP has a partner (Tellus Education Group, Education&Mobility, Training Vision, Berlink and Cap Ulysse) that will support the organization / preparation, monitoring and evaluation of the placements, which will be adapted to the participants areas of training.
In terms of results, it is expected that this project allows participants to increase their employability skills, being quickly integrated into the labour market (comparing with non-participants) and that staff members update their technical knowledge.
In terms of organization, it is expected that these activities and subsequent learning contribute to the modernization and innovation of the organization itself and the services it provides, empowering ATEP´s image as a dynamic, forward-looking institution, with Europe on the horizon. 
Finally, it is expected that, long-term, this project will reinforce work methodologies and international exchange, enabling experiences that make the difference in students' lives, both professionally and personally.

Ogre Technical School’s strategic aim is, in co-operation with the industry associations, businesses and professional organizations, to introduce and implement innovative solutions for vocational education by raising the quality of vocational education according to the employers' requirements, including the development of new and update of the existing educational programs, build international partnerships between educational institutions and industry organizations by promoting the internationalization of the educational institution.
The project "Wisdom-in knowledge, strength-in work" will be implemented with the aim:
1) to increase the Ogre Technical School’s students professional skills and ability to a level that is appropriate in today's labour market requirements, strengthen cooperation between the educational institution and international companies. 38 2nd, 3rd and 4th year students of computer science, electronics, administrative work, forestry, art and design, hotel and restaurant service areas will be involved in the project;
2) to contribute to the improvement of educational quality, excellence and internationalization in Ogre Technical School by improving teaching abilities and skills of teachers and teaching staff. The project will involve 7 teachers and / or teaching staff, representing the educational programs of Electronics and Computer Science (1), Multimedia design (1), Visual media and art (1) Advertising design (1) Accounting and administrative work (1), Catering (1), Hospitality (1).

In the result of the project the students and teachers/ teaching staff of Ogre Technical School will:
1) improve the educational environment and learning;
2) enhance career opportunities; 
3) promote personal growth;
4) improve foreign language skills;
5) promote intercultural understanding;
6) increase the motivation to continue to participate in projects and to educate further after the mobility abroad; 
7) improve the skills related to professional activities;
8) increase the motivation and satisfaction of daily work.
 
Students, teachers and teaching staff mobility, participation in the international project, finding new cooperation contacts, improvement of the foreign language knowledge and expertise will contribute to the development of Ogre Technical School’s internationalization, improve the quality of education, innovation, excellence, foster co-operation between the educational institution and the employers, both locally and internationally.
For a successful implementation of the project and achievement of the results five partners from Hungary, Spain, Italy, Portugal and England are involved. Duration of the practice program 14 to 28 days, experience exchange program – 7 days. Project will be implemented from October 2017 to November 2018.

The main objective of the project is to create new opportunities for learners / trainees of  vocational courses at Vila Verde Secondary School, as well as for staff (teachers of vocational training courses), creating new working tools for their present professional reality (teachers ) and future professional life (students).
Some objectives were set out:
-To Increase the employability and life skills of VET students and thereby contribute for our country's competitiveness in the European economy; 
 -To Support  the strengthening of European cooperation in Vocational Education and Training (objectives of the Bruges Communiqué); 
- To Develop tolerance for multiculturalism;
- To Abolish stereotypes; 
- To Develop self-confidence; 
- To Recognize the differences in the different places of work of different countries; 
- Reinforce the learning of foreign languages, particularly in the use of English; 
- Improve skills in ICT; Improving the communication skills of learners; 
- To GIve learners the opportunity to choose the country in which they would like to work; Integrate students with special needs; Give students a European view of the world in the labor market.
 The Activities / mobilities were programmed with 5 partner institutions for 4 weeks,  from five different countries, Italy, Spain and the United Kingdom, Ireland and Bulgaria. This project was planned immediately after the beginning of the school year, a team of 4 teachers, 2 elements of the management and an element of administrative services began to define the areas of professional intervention in the region and four professional training courses were selected, Tourism, Health and Commerce and Informatics. The number of students was defined for the 4 professional areas, 28 students who will participate in the mobility activities during two years. The choice of participants in the project was carefully elaborated; The selection process was open to juniors, seniors and recent graduates.  Mobility activities will be articulated with the trainees' curricula in Portugal, so their internship abroad would be planned among all the partners. Everything will be carefully planned and students will have to attend the language preparation to be well prepared and feel well integrated during the internship. All groups of trainees during mobilities will go with an accompanying person  since most of them are under 18 and two are special education students. The person accompanying them will go with the students to the places where they will move, they will make sure of the housing conditions,they  will supervise their place of work and will ensure that all the conditions established in the learning contract are fulfilled, in the the end of the activity  the accompanying teacher will bring the students back to their country. 
The Activities will be divided into two academic years:
 2017- 2018 - Mobility 14 trainee students ; Spain (Málaga) 4 trainee students  (2 Health and 2 Trade) 11th form- 30 days; United Kingdom (Portsmouth) 4  trainee students (Information Technology) 11th form - 30 days;
- Italy (Rimini) 4 trainee students (Tourism and Health); 2 recent graduates in Tourism - 12 weeks; 2 students of 12th form of Health - 30 days;
 2018/2019 Mobility 14 trainees
 - Italy (Rimini) 4 trainees 11th and 12th form (Tourism and Health) -30 days; United Kingdom (Portsmouth) - 4 trainee students  (2 Health and 2 Tourism ) - 30 days; Bulgaria (Sofia) - 6 trainee students 11 and 12 form (2 Tourism, 2 Health, 2 IT) - 30 days.
The diversity of training places and of vocational areas presented will add an extra-value to our project and will make our school and our region  richer  and more attractive.
For supervision and dissemination we will create a website and a blog where students will be monitored in their work activities during their international mobility activity, they will communicate through email, chat, facebook, skype with their peers and with their supervisors and at the  End they will produce an ebook with all the activities carried out during the internship.
Finally, an event will be organized by all participants on European Day, May 9, or on the week of Europe including face or skype conferences  with MEPs from the region, thus promoting once again the feeling of belonging to a Globalizing European Community .
The evaluation will be done at the end in order to improve and make productive all the work produced and  contributing   for the good practices that can  be achieved by all. The ECVET system will be implemented.
With the development of this project, our students will become more aware that we as Europeans,  have a lot in common, but we are also very different, and that reality is really fascinating.

The I.MOVE - Mobility, Employability and Empowerment in Europe Project is a reflection of the active participation of the school community of EPAVE – Escola Profissional do Alto Ave, in the development of a strategy that enhances the employability of young people through European mobility based on three supports: mobility, employability and the citizens’ empowerment.
Located in the heart of Minho, EPAVE was born in 1995 in Póvoa de Lanhoso, with the mission of creating professional education of quality based on human, cultural and social values. Believing that the great capital of mankind is sustained by the knowledge and personal formation of each one, and that new technologies foster real spaces of knowledge and information, EPAVE promotes the necessary methods and techniques for personal development anchored to the latest advances. EPAVE recognizes Europe as a mean of multiple learning opportunities and a space for human achievement.
Thus, the choice of the acronym I.MOVE focuses the power that resides in "I as a citizen" and freedom of movement in the search for a more active and conscious, autonomous and responsible European role. Furthermore, this project aims to promote the empowerment movement through synergetic partnerships that will spread the social, cultural, linguistic and professional competences, allowing the growth and professional development of its participants in the European space.
I.MOVE is aimed at students of professional courses in the areas of Industrial Maintenance - Automotive Mechatronics; Electronics and Telecommunications, Fashion Coordination and Production, Renewable Energies, Environmental and Rural Tourism and Communication, Marketing, Public Relations and Advertising. The project also includes EPAVE's training staff who, in a team work, promote quality professional training, thus maintaining the students' motivation for vocational education and, consequently, a better integration into the labour market.
We set out the objectives of the project:
- Provide a European dimension in learning / teaching;
- Facilitate personal development, social integration and the exercise of active European citizenship;
- Promote employability in the European labour market;
- Value vocational education and training, regarding another way of teaching;
- Reduce school drop-out and social exclusion, particularly in the region where we are inserted;
- Promote motivation for lifelong learning;
- Improve technical skills through a comparison of knowledge and experience in institutional contexts in the host countries;
- Improve language skills;
- Enrich transversal competences: skills, knowledge and experiences essential for professional success in a knowledge society;
- Understand the business and teaching reality of other EU countries and understand professional performance in another socio-economic context;
- Create technical and technological synergies with other European professionals;
- Increase the volume of mobility within the European area of pupils and staff;
- Enrich Curricula Vitae with the certification of acquired competences;
- Improve EPAVE´s Educational Project with measures to fight against school dropout and school failure;
- Observe and analyse pilot project of dual / tutored training to replicate in school.

The mobility project "Development of Professional and Professional Skills and Entrepreneurship Competence in the Valga County Vocational Training Center" is aimed at students and employees of the Valga County Vocational Training Center. Within the framework of the project, 56 pupils from different curricula can take their internships in a foreign country and traineeships for 9 teachers can take place. 10 employees are familiar with schools.
The goal of the project is to:
• raise the vocational and professional skills of students and staff, increase the level of openness, develop the creativity of students and teachers, with the help of which the school can implement the strategy and objectives of the Estonian Lifelong Learning 2020 at the Valga County Vocational Training Center;
• To integrate theoretical knowledge in performing practical activities and apprenticeships;
• Improve the quality of teaching on the basis of a new learning path and curve methologies;
• Contribute to the harmonization of the level of vocational training provided by the Valga Center for Vocational Education and Training
The activities of the project will be reflected on the school's website, where you can read the mobility blogs and summaries. Project activities are reflected on the school's website and in the social media channels (such as the school's Facebook channel). In order to increase awareness about the mobility, at least one story of the movement is published in the traditional school's special edition supplement published regularlyin the South Estonia Postimees regional newspaper (on paper and digitally).

The initiator of the project "Education through work for successful professional realization" is Svishtov Vocational High School “Aleko Konstantinov”. This draft provides implementation of four mobilities of different target groups:
1: 7 students, profession "Restaurant keeper"-a three-week manufacturing practice in Rimini, Italy in July 2019;
2: 7 students, profession " Electrical and power engineering” a three-week manufacturing practice in Portsmouth, UK in April 2019;
3: 7 students, profession "Furniture manufacture"-a three-week manufacturing practice in Berlin, Germany in July 2019;
4: 8 teachers in vocational training-a one-week mobility in Berlin, Germany in July 2019.
The proposal is aimed at the objectives of the program: Support students in acquiring competencies (knowledge, skills, attitudes) in order to improve their personal self-development and employability on the European labour market and increase their foreign language competence. Support professional development of the people who work in the field of education, training and youth in order to stimulate innovations and improve the quality of teaching and learning.
The implementation of the project activities is aimed to:
-Expanding professional knowledge and skills in a real working environment;
-Promoting language learning and acquiring communication skills in a foreign language;
-Supporting personal development, employability of the users and their better adaptability on the European labour market;
-Expanding knowledge of the participants about different cultures and countries and creating a network of international contacts;
-Supporting professional development of teachers and encouraging the usage of innovations and implementation of European experience in dual education;
-Increasing the quality of VET, the mobility of users and striving for continuous professional self-development, improvement;
-Increasing the prestige and self-confidence of teachers.
In order to implement the project activities the school will collaborate with three partner organizations from the host countries:  Sistema Turismo-Italy, Training Vision-Great Britain and Berlink-Germany. The project partners will allocate the responsibilities in order to achieve quality in the accomplishment of the mobility. They will cooperate with issuing of Europass certificates and implementing of ECVET procedures.
Expected results:
Students: Acquired professional knowledge and skills in a real working environment; Acquired language knowledge and communication skills in a foreign language; Acquired social skills for adapting in a multicultural environment; Acquired knowledge for the way of living and work in EU country; Gained experience for personal self-development and employability on the EU's labour market in long term; Increased self-reliance of users; Increased motivation for participation in further education and training.
For students the conduction of practical training in EU country will lead to the acquisition of professional skills in a real working environment. It will contribute for the formation of striving for professional development, will increase activity for successful realization, will motivate professional and personal development. The language learning and it’s practicing in a real language environment will improve communication skills. Acquaintance with another culture will increase the chances for successful adaptation and realization on the European labor market. Students will increase their self-confidence, motivation to participate in future training, will enhance employability and better career prospects.
Teachers: Achieved qualification for implementation of European experience in dual education; Improved quality of teaching and training by applying European experience; Acquired language skills in German and English; Increased motivation for participation in future training; Increased prestige and self-confidence of teachers.
Mobility will form striving for professional development and improvement of users. Acquired knowledge, acquaintance with European experience and its sharing will contribute to the use of new teaching methods and training programs, adapted to innovations in profession, increasing students’ motivation and improving the quality of VET. In long term this will reduce the number of early school leavers, will increase the prestige of the school as an educational institution, will attract employers in the educational process, will give opportunities for better realization on the labor market, will expand the network of international contacts, will improve the national and international profile of the school, will make it a preferred partner in future mobility with other countries and partners.
This project will give opportunities for effective cooperation in the field of VET. Promoting the acquired knowledge, skills and competencies will increase motivation for learning, quality of VET and successful realization on the EU's labour market.
